This paper is about congestion control in computer networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer networking (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the behavior of a specific end-to-end protocol, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and systems and control theory (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper analyzes the convergence rates of the protocol, which is related to distributed computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper discusses the throughput of the network, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM).
